      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/51/13",
      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا اَلْحَسَنِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنْ رَجُلٍ لَهُ مَمْلُوكٌ قَدْ أَبَقَ مِنْهُ يَجُوزُ أَنْ يُعْتِقَهُ فِي كَفَّارَةِ اَلظِّهَارِ قَالَ \"لاَ بَأْسَ بِهِ مَا لَمْ يَعْرِفْ مِنْهُ مَوْتاً\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3527 - It is narrated from Abu Hashim al-Ja'fari, who said:\n\"I asked Abu al-Hasan (as), about a man who had a runaway slave. Is it permissible for him to free the slave as an expiation for zihar?\"\nImam (as) replied: 'There is no harm in it, as long as he has not come to know of the slave's death.'\""
        ]
      }
    },
